label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 467: Khawāṣ al-manāzil wa-al-shuhūr wa-al-anwāʻā
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Work on the use of astronomical observations to predict weather changes in order to determine the best times to sow and harvest in northern Africa. The text is divided into 12 chapters describing weather variations for each of the 12 European months, using their European names.
        Language: Arabic
        Support: paper
        Extent: 
        Collation: 
        Layout: Written in 24-28 long lines; inner margins marked by folding or drypoint.
        Script: Written in an andalusi script, probably by a single hand, with additions in a second hand at the beginning of the manuscript (p. 1).
        Decoration: 
        Binding: Later morocco, blind-tooled, spine repaired.
        Origin: Written in northern Africa or Spain in the 14th century.
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 467
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5185355 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5185355
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs467.html
